news.article_text:
Zoetis (ZTS) stock took a hit Tuesday after the animal health outlet slashed its 2025 sales outlook on the back of "broader macro trends and operational environment."

For the year, the company now projects $9.4 billion to $9.475 billion, representing organic operational growth of 5.5% to 6.5%. At the midpoint, that's down $87.5 million from the view issued three months ago.
